<item>
            <title>[HBASE-2609] Harmonize the Get and Delete operations</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/HBASE-2609</link>
                <project id="12310753" key="HBASE">HBase</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;In my work on &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/HBASE-2400&quot; title=&quot;new connector for Avro RPC access to HBase cluster&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;HBASE-2400&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;HBASE-2400&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;, implementing deletes for the Avro server felt quite awkward. Rather than the clean API of the Get object, which allows restrictions on the result set from a row to be expressed with addColumn, addFamily, setTimeStamp, setTimeRange, setMaxVersions, and setFilters, the Delete object hides these semantics behind various constructors to deleteColumn&lt;span class=&quot;error&quot;&gt;&amp;#91;s&amp;#93;&lt;/span&gt; an deleteFamily. From my naive vantage point, I see no reason why it would be a bad idea to mimic the Get API exactly, though I could quite possibly be missing something. Thoughts?&lt;/p&gt;</description>
